tasks: launch, describe, stop, stop_all, checkout, make, run_at 

normal workflow:     launch, checkout, make, run_at, stop
additional helpers:  describe, stop_all

cap launch -s build=
  launches a new instance based on your build in the config file.  it will print 
  the instance id, which is necessary for other steps

cap checkout -s build=   -s inst_id=
  checks out repo on instance 
  repo specified in config file via build arg

cap make -s inst_id=
  makes repo on instance
  repo specified in config file via build arg

cap run_at -s inst_id=    -s build=
  runs tests, dumps results to results_path
  repo specified in config file via build arg

cap stop -s inst_id
  stops instance

cap describe
  describes all running instances to stdout

cap stop_all
  stops all instances

NOTES:
script assumes config file in location config/build.yml
you will also need to specify capfile on command line: "-f capfile.rb" 





